The article is a joint statement from multiple governments expressing their support for United Nations peacekeeping operations. The governments, including Bangladesh, Brazil, China, France, Germany, Japan, the United States, and others, commend the bravery of the men and women serving in UN peacekeeping operations and honor those who have sacrificed their lives. They recognize the increasing complexity and danger faced by peacekeepers and pledge to assist the United Nations in mobilizing the necessary support for these operations. The governments also acknowledge the need for critical reforms to strengthen peacekeeping operations in response to evolving security threats. They support the Secretary-General's strategic review and commit to providing the funding, forces, equipment, training, and capabilities needed for UN peacekeeping operations. The governments call on other countries to join them in demonstrating support for UN peacekeeping operations and commit to reconvening in one year to assess progress and catalyze additional commitments.